languageTools.program.agent.precompilation

Class PreCompiler<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • languageTools.program.agent.precompilation.PreCompiler<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GOALProgramPreCompiler, RulePreCompiler

    public abstract class PreCompiler<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Basic structure for a precompilation class. The intended structure for subclasses is as follows:
    • Create a subclass for each type of object to be precompiled, with custom code for #doPrecompile in each of them.
    • If an object to be precompiled contains (links to) other objects to be precompiled, call #doPrecompile on a precompilator for that object.
    Author:
    K.Hindriks

      • PreCompiler

        protected PreCompiler()
        Create a new PreCompiler. Does nothing; the error and warning lists are initialized by calling preCompile(T) (or initialize(), which is called by preCompile(T)).

      • preCompile

        public final boolean preCompile(T subject)
        Precompiles a certain object.
        Multiple objects can be precompiled with this precompilator, but information about previously precompiled objects is lost once a new one is precompiled.
        Parameters:
        subject - The object to precompile.
        Returns:
        true iff the given object is 'perfect'. That is, if no errors or warnings were reported while precompiling the object. Note that this also returns false if the given object is valid but still has some warnings.
